text=https://i.imgur.com/WTCZurQ.png%0a(:include GameRef.Directoryhelp:)%0a----%0a%25center%25https://i.imgur.com/003gTYc.png%0a----%0a[[#top]]%0a(:toc:)%0a%0aThis guide has been created to lead you through creating a character for Chronicles of Darkness: Pittsburgh. This guide applies to all characters, however, there are venue specific character creation rules cited throughout. Half-template (%25geist%25Absent, %25vampire%25Ghouls, %25vampire%25Dhampir, and %25werewolf%25Wolf-Blooded%25silver%25) character creation rules are addressed under their parent venues.%0a%0a!%25center%25'''Book Policy'''%0a%0aSee [[Book Policy]] for approved resources.%0a%0a!%25center%25'''Guidelines for All Characters'''%0a%0a*Chronicle%0a**Select: Pittsburgh, PA%0a*Age%0a**All characters must be (and appear to be) 18 years or older. See [[SitePoliciesAndPractices|Site Policies And Practices]].%0a*Free Bonuses%0a**Certain traits (abilities, merits, etc.) grant additional bonuses elsewhere such as a bonus specialty or +1 to an attribute. If your character is granted a bonus, make note of it in your POWER NOTES section of the character sheet as well as adding it to your sheet.%0a%0a!!%25center%25Z-Splats%0a%0aZ-Splats (Lodges, Bloodlines) can be taken at creation if prerequisites are met (see [[Z-Splats]] for rules). This must be justified in the character's background.%0a%0a(:table table border=0 cellpadding=5 cellspacing=0:)%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a!%25center%25'''Character Demographics and Background'''%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a:Name:%0aEnter the character's name.%0a*For ease of use, it is a best practice to use standard alphanumeric characters.%0a:Nicknames: If a character is generally referred to by a nickname instead of their first name, enter the nickname for the first name.%0a:Alternate Identity: If a character has an Alternate Identity they go by publicly that is different from their actual name, use that. (i.e., James Cooper goes by Johnathan Tucker as he's in witness protection)%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a:%25werewolf%25Werewolves Only:%0a:%25silver%25Deed Name: The Deed Name should be entered in hyphens between the first and last name: Jane -Dances With Humans- Doe%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a:Age: If it varies, enter the character's '''true''' age, not apparent age.%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a%25right%25[[#top|&#8593; back to top]]%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a!!%25center%25''Affiliations''%0a%0aThis area contains unique fields for each Character Type. Use the Drop Downs to select. Below are listed some specific explanations.%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a:%25vampire%25Ghoul Only:%25%25%0aFill in the applicable Clan of your character's Regnant.%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a:%25vampire%25Dhampir Only:%25%25%0aFill in the applicable Clan of your character's Parent.%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a%25right%25[[#top|&#8593; back to top]]%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a!!%25center%25''Biography and Notes''%0a%0aCompose a biography that identifies in written form or bullet point the history of your character that addresses the following:%0a%0a*Significant events or overall experience in childhood or adolescence%0a*Significant events or overall experience in adulthood (relationships, professions, traumas, successes, etc.)%0a*Significant events or experiences which lead towards the character obtaining specialized merits (professional training, contacts, allies, etc.), abilities or statistics. Items which require this will be noted in this guide.%0a*If applicable, when the character moved to Miami including any significant events or motivations around the move. \\%0aIf you compose a biography which is more than 5-7 paragraphs, you must also include a bullet pointed summary of all key points.%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a:Supernatural Only:%0a*Events surrounding becoming a supernatural character (embrace, first change, death, etc.)%0a*Significant events or overall experience after becoming a supernatural character (joining covenant, tribe, coterie, etc.)%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a:%25mortal%25Mortal/+ Only:%25%25%0a*If applicable, events surrounding becoming aware of the supernatural including which factions or spheres they are currently aware of%0a*Significant events or overall experience after becoming aware of the supernatural%0a*If applicable, events surrounding joining any groups or becoming associated with particular Factions.%0a%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a!!%25center%25''Banned Backgrounds/Concepts''%0a%0aPlease be aware that the following backgrounds or concepts are not allowed:%0a%0a*Anachronistic or over-the-top concepts. (Ninja, serial killer, Queen of England)%0a*Recreations of signature characters of any book, film or other popular fiction.%0a*Direct recreation of any actual person, living or dead.%0a*Characters already played by you or another person during WW6 or currently on another site. See [[SitePoliciesAndPractices | Site Policies And Practices]].%0a*Antagonist concepts (Pure, VII, etc.). This includes characters that are innately antagonistic to other PC splats (werewolves that hunt all vampires, for instance).%0a*Backgrounds which include rape or child abuse. See [[[SitePoliciesAndPractices#toc12| Site Policies And Practices]].%0a%0a!!%25center%25''Notes''%0aThis field is primarily to note any bonus items gained from the purchase of other traits (Such as Professional Training, MCI and other things that grant extra powers). Power notes is used for starting spends and bonuses and anything that is unchanging, Player Notes are used for editable things such as bonuses from MCIs and group merits such as a joint Safe Place.%0a%0a:%25geist%25Geist Only:%25%25%0aInclude a description of your Liminal Aura and the method of death which will permanently kill the Bound in the Power Notes section.%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a%25right%25[[#top|&#8593; back to top]]%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a!%25center%25'''Stats'''%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a!!%25center%25''Attributes''%0a%0aUnlike the RAW Character Creation, we do not limit Attribute point allocation at Character Creation to 5/4/3. All Attributes begin at 1 for free.  '''Total dots to spend are 12'''%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a:Attribute 4+: This must be explained in Biography or Notes.%0a:Attribute 1: This must be explained in Biography or Notes.%0a%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a:%25geist%25Geist Only:%25%25%0a:Geist:%0aRemember that Geists need to have their Name, Attributes, Virtue/Vice, Triggers, Rank, Ban, Bane, and Key listed, among any other special traits. This goes in the "Geist" box at the bottom of the sheet.%0a%0a:Remembrance Trait: Must be something available at character creation normally.%0a%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a!!%25center%25''Skills''%0a%0aUnlike the RAW Character Creation, we do not limit Skill point allocation at Character Creation to 11/7/4. '''Total dots to spend are 22'''%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a:Skill 4+: This must be explained in Biography or Notes.%0a%0a:Occult Specialties: This must be explained in Biography or Notes. Specialties in other Character Types represent significant "insider" knowledge and requires a detailed and fitting explanation.%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a%25right%25[[#top|&#8593; back to top]]%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a!%25center%25'''Traits'''%0a%0a:%25red%25NOTE:%25%25%0aCertain traits (abilities, merits, etc.) grant additional bonuses elsewhere such as a bonus specialty or +1 to an attribute. If your character is granted a bonus, put those free things on your sheet as well as marking them down in your Power Notes section. List the traits name and include what you have added from what the trait grants. Example: Professional Training.%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a!!%25center%25''Abilities''%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a:All:%0a:Cost Breaks: Merits and powers providing Experience cost breaks do not apply to character creation unless they explicitly say so (which includes applying retroactively).%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a:%25geist%25Geist Only:%25%25%0a:Synergy:%0a*3 must be explained in Biography or Notes.%0a*4+ is not allowed at Character Creation.%0a:Affinity Abilities:%0a*Check the "Affinity" box for all Affinity (Burden) Haunts and the Memento box for any Keys that come from Mementos.%0a%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a:%25geist%25Absent Only:%0a:Memories: Do not fill in Memory Skills, list them in your Power Notes. %0a:Attributes: These work by the book for Absent.%0a:Skills: Remember that Absent do not get the normal Skill allotment. %0a:Numina and Manifestations: Only Numina from the core and Geist are available. Absent may not take any Numina or Manifestations that have to do with the Shadow.  %0a:Anchors: (Solid) PCs can be Anchors for Absent. NPCs need to be discussed with the Storymasters. %0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a:%25vampire%25Vampire Only:%0a:Blood Potency:%0a*3 must be explained in Biography or Notes.%0a*4+ is not allowed at Character Creation.%0a:Non-Affinity Abilities:%0a*Out of Clan Disciplines have their own section on the sheet%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a:%25werewolf%25Werewolf Only:%25%25%0a:Primal Urge:%0a*3 must be explained in Biography or Notes.%0a*4+ is not allowed at Character Creation.%0a:Non-Affinity Abilities:%0a*Check the "NA" box for all Non-Affinity Gifts.%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a:%25werewolf%25Wolf-Blooded Only:%0a:Tells: Tells are capped at 4 total at creation, with those after the first purchased as a merit normally.%0a%0a*The following Tells are only available at Character Creation as they are Tells present from birth:%0a**Moon Marked%0a**Second Skin%0a**Shadow Twin%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a%25right%25[[#top|&#8593; back to top]]%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a!!%25center%25''Merits''%0a%0aAll Merit purchases at Character Creation must meet the Prerequisites in the RAW. Unlike the RAW Character Creation, we do not limit merits to 7 for Mortals and 10 for supernatural.  '''Everyone gets 10 points for Merits.''' The following general Merit guidelines are applicable to all merits except where listed under the specific Merit type.%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a:Merit 4+: This must be explained in Biography or Notes.%0a:Scaled Merit 4+: without a listed pre-requisite: Limited to 2 at Character Creation.%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a:%25mortal%25Mortal Only:%0a:The following Merit Templates are available:%0a*Atariya (HL)%0a*Plain (HL)%0a*Lost Boys (HL)%0a*Psychic Vampires (HL)%0a*Psychics (SS: TE)%0a*Shadow Occultists (SbtM)%0a*Skin Thieves (DE)%0a*Thaumaturges (SS: TE)%0a**The first dot (or lowest, if it starts over 1) in the defining merit of the minor template is free.%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a:Supernatural Merits: Ghouls, Wolf-Blooded and Absent are not eligible for Supernatural Merits listed in Chronicles of Darkness.%0a%0aDhampir are eligible.%0a%0a%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a%25right%25[[#top|&#8593; back to top]]%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a!!! Mental Merits%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a:Professional Training: Can only be taken once.%0a*Use the Notes section under Character Bio to identify the merit or skill benefits obtained by this merit as well as adding them to your sheet.%0a*Select two applicable Asset Skills if your Profession is not listed in the RAW, and there is not a close approximation.%0a**Professional Training is a MUNDANE merit. You may not take it for blatantly supernatural "jobs" like "monster hunter" or a covenant/tribal position. Occult Investigator and similar that would be reflected in the real world are fine.%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a!!!%25center%25''Social Merits''%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a:Allies, Contacts, Mentor: This must be explained in Biography or Notes.%0a*In the Merit Notes include the Sphere which the Allies, Contact or Mentor represents. As in: Contacts: (City Hall/Government) Mayor's Office%0a%0a:[[City.MysteryCult|Mystery Cult Initiation]]: See the [[Cult System]] for forming a Mystery Cult as part of a player-level group. You may only be in one. %0a*Use the Notes section under Character Bio to identify the merit or skill benefits obtained by this merit as well as adding them to your sheet.%0a%0a:Resources 3+: This must be explained in Biography or Notes.%0a%0a:Status: This merit can only be purchased up to 2 at creation.%0a*Vampires get a free dot in their Clan or Covenant.%0a%0a*The following Spheres are available for purchasing status:%0a**Arts and Society%0a**Business%0a**Crime%0a**Education%0a**Law and Order%0a**Media%0a**Medical%0a*'''Shadow''' - Status in this Sphere cannot be purchased at Character Creation.%0a*'''Underworld''' - Status in this Sphere cannot be purchased at Character Creation.%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a!!!%25center%25''Physical Merits''%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a:Fighting Style at 3+: Limited to 1 instance at Character Creation. You may have other Styles at 1-2 dots.%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a%25right%25[[#top|&#8593; back to top]]%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a!%25center%25'''Influences'''%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a!!%25center%25''Anchors''%0a%0aFor Virtue and Vice, Root and Bloom, Mask and Dirge, or Blood and Bone fill in the name for each.%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a:Touchstone: For supernatural characters that have them, this should be listed in the appropriate spot on the bottom of the sheet or in Power Notes, and described in the background. %0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a!!%25center%25''Aspirations''%0a%0aSee [[SitePoliciesAndPractices|Site Policies And Practices]] for Aspirations help.%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a:Short Term Aspiration: Choose two short-term aspirations.%0a:Long term Aspiration: Choose one long-term aspiration.%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a:%25geist%25Geist Only:%25%25%0a:Burden Aspiration: This is what has brought your character back from the dead and is their ultimate goal for their second chance at life.  It can be as simple or complex as you like, ranging from finding the person who murdered you to ensuring that a loved one is taken care of in the long-term.  The simpler the aspiration, however, the easier it will be for your character to fulfill their purpose and move on.  As this chronicle is expected to last two to three years, keep that in mind when choosing this Aspiration.%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a!!%25center%25''Integrity and equivalents''%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a:%25mortal%25Mortal Only:%25%25%0a:Questionnaire: These questions need to be answered in addition to the Biography and Notes. This identifies your breaking points%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a:%25geist%25Geist Only:%25%25%0a:Crisis Points: List any unique one with your Geist notes. %0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a:Note: You never have to make breaking point/detachment/etc rolls for things that happened before sanctioning (for example, a vampire that has Cruac).%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a%25right%25[[#top|&#8593; back to top]]%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a!!%25center%25''Equipment''%0a%0aAdd any equipment plus applicable modifiers to your character sheet.%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a:Availability 1-3: Some leeway is given for a few items at this cost even without Resources.%0a%0a:Availability 4+: Requires Resources or another appropriate merit at 3+ unless a very good reason can be given in your Biography.%0a%0a:Carried: In Equipment Note, identify which items are typically Carried.%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a!!%25center%25''Starting XP''%0a%0aSee the [[GameRef.Experience|Experience Guide]] for current starting XP levels. Spend it using the guidelines provided up to this point (e.g. no Supernatural Tolerance over 3, etc).%0a%0a(:cellnr width=100%25:)%0a%0a%25right%25[[#top|&#8593; back to top]]%0a%0a(:tableend:)%0a%0a%0a!%25center%25'''Other Links'''%0a%0aSee [[Sanctioning]] for assistance in what we look for.%0a%0aSee [[House Rules]] for custom rules which might affect a character.%0a%0a!!%25center%25'''Wiki Templates'''%0a%0aHere are some templates for players to work off of:%0a%0a*[[GameRef.MortalTemplate | Mortal+ Template]] \\%0a*[[GameRef.WerewolfTemplate | Werewolf Template ]] \\%0a*[[GameRef.WolfbloodTemplate | Wolfblood Template ]] \\%0a*[[GameRef.GeistTemplate | Geist Template ]] \\%0a*[[GameRef.AbsentTemplate | Absent Template ]] \\%0a*[[GameRef.VampireTemplate | Vampire Template ]] \\%0a*[[GameRef.DhampirTemplate | Dhampir Template ]] \\%0a*[[GameRef.GhoulTemplate | Ghoul Template ]]%0a%0a%25right%25[[#top|&#8593; back to top]]%0a%0a(:include GameRef.Directoryhelp:)%0a%0a%0a
